description: This is a story about the events in one day of a cinnamon squirrel
At 6:00 AM, cinnamon left early for foraging. Foraging needs to happen early in the day.
By 10:00 AM the foraging had been completed. It was time for recreation. Cinnamon headed to the nearest tree.
Anxious to find an oak tree in particular, Cinnamon kept up the pace, running through the park areas in search of the goal.

When an oak tree was located, Cinnamon celebrated. Scampering up and down was the next move. Qualitative data analysts recorded this motion as "scampering" but Cinnamon had another take on the nature of movement.
Cinnamon headed back to the home base area. A time of rest was at hand.
and then another night in the trees of Central Park.
